CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 15, 1966, pg. 12A reads: "Schenley High Champs-Listening to the words of Coach Willard Fisher (far left), are these eight youngsters, who comprise the basic personnel of last year's City League titlists, in Section One. From left to right, they are Anthony Austin, Jake Williams, Jim Prince, Montell Brundage, Ken Durrett, Marv Snowden, Charles Burley and Ed Gibson.  The group posed for the Courier just before launching their 1966 campaign. (Harris Photo)"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Schenley High School basketball team, from left: #12 Anthony Austin, #52 Jacob Williams Jr., #42 Jimmy Prince, #32 Montell Brundage, #54 Kenny Durrett, #24 Marvin Snowden, #30 Charley Burley, and #50 Edward "Petey" Gibson, posed holding basketballs in Schenley High School gymnasium
